gomodel:SYNGO_1087  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Quantitative proteomic comparisons indicates an enrichment of MAL2 in synaptic vesicles that harbour vGlut-1 and would store glutamate. An antibody that shows specificity for MAL-2 based on peptide antigen competition is used. Western blotting of synaptic subcellular fractions, immunofluoresence co-localization with synaptic vesicle markers, immunogold electron labelling of purified synaptic vesicles and within intact tissue all evidence MAL-2 as a bona-fide synaptic vesicle membrane protein.. Experimental description: Rat tissue is largely used as explicitly stated in Methods: Male Wistar rats (300-350g) but figures mention mouse hippocampal and cerebellar sections (e.g. figure 8). Citation to previous papers in the immunoisolation section of materials and methods would suggest that immuno-isolation of synaptic vesicles used rat as starting material." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1087" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

